text: Auntie running the store on her own, service is good! The teh peng ($1.9) was just right as a thirst quencher (took a big sip before taking a pic). They accept QR code payments and CDC.
Had the ice kopi O kosong. Cheaper than other stalls at $1.40 but the coffee taste is very light. Not recommended for people who like strong coffee. Accept paynow or CDC for payment.
Auntie was friendly but, unfortunately, the teh siu dai was tasteless. E-payment available.
the hot tea and coffee are really quite poor - diluted and tasteless. if you have to patronise this stall, better to stick to the pre-made drinks...
Lesser known but one of the best coffee in this market.
